You are an expert developer working on _n0 (pronounced "n-zero"), a Next.js 16+ fullstack application.

BEFORE writing ANY code, you MUST read the architecture guide:
- For full context: read all files in .ai/sections/
- For quick reference: read .ai/CONTEXT.md
- For specific tasks: check .ai/INDEX.md for which sections to read

CRITICAL RULES (never violate):

1. DEPENDENCY TREE:
   packages → 0 internal deps
   shared   → can import packages only
   client   → can import shared + packages
   server   → can import shared + packages
   app      → can import everything
   
   ❌ client NEVER imports server
   ❌ server NEVER imports client
   ❌ shared NEVER imports client or server
   ❌ packages NEVER imports anything internal

2. FILE PLACEMENT:
   Types          → src/shared/types/entities/
   Zod schemas    → src/shared/schemas/
   Utils          → src/shared/utils/
   Constants      → src/shared/constants/
   DB queries     → src/server/db/queries/
   Services       → src/server/services/
   Server actions → src/server/actions/
   API routes     → app/api/
   UI primitives  → src/client/components/ui/
   Shared comps   → src/client/components/common/
   Feature comps  → src/client/components/features/{name}/
   Layout comps   → src/client/components/layout/
   Hooks          → src/client/hooks/{common|features}/
   Stores         → src/client/stores/
   Pages          → app/({group})/{route}/page.tsx

3. PATTERNS:
   - Services return Result<T> (Ok/Err pattern)
   - API routes use success()/error() helpers
   - Server actions return { data } or { error }
   - Zod schemas validate on BOTH client and server
   - Types are derived (Pick, Partial, z.infer), NEVER duplicated
   - "use client" ONLY when needed (events, hooks, state)
   - Pages are STUPID assemblers — no logic

4. NAMING:
   - Files: kebab-case (number-card.tsx)
   - Components: PascalCase (NumberCard)
   - Functions: camelCase (formatPrice)
   - Constants: UPPER_CASE (APP_CONFIG)
   - Types: PascalCase (PhoneNumber)
   - Suffixes: .types.ts, .schema.ts, .service.ts, .queries.ts, .store.ts, .error.ts

5. FEATURE CREATION ORDER:
   types → schemas → enums → constants → queries → services → actions → API → hooks → stores → components → pages

Always check .ai/sections/15-checklist-before-generating-code.md before finishing.
